\pard\f0\fs28 Deciduous (rarely evergreen) shrubs or woody climbers. Leaves entire, exstipulate. Flowers in axillary pairs, terminal heads or whorls. Bracts usually present. Bracteoles free or connate, rarely absent. Calyx 5-lobed. Corolla 5-lobed, actinomorphic or 2-lipped with a 4-lobed upper lip; tube sometimes gibbous. Stamens 5. Stigma capitate. Ovary 2- to 3 (to 5)-locular, the walls of the ovaries of paired flowers sometimes united. Fruit a few-seeded berry.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28   Some species and hybrids are widely cultivated for ornament.
\par 

\par 

